Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from scammers who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by "Kommersant" with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator gave telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, operators found a number replacement.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction on the use of financial services was set.
Deputy Head of the Department of Information Security of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced with the change of the number.
He explained that the operators do not always respond to the warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, citing the lack of such an obligation in the law "On Communications".
In the bank "Otkritie", Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the change of the number.
As reported in the press service of "Beeline", part of the information about fraudulent calls, which was transmitted by the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudsters’ numbers, to which the telecom operator will contact every call to check the number.
He explained that in order to establish such a base, it would be necessary to amend the legislation.
