According to the agronomist, the consumer can not get reliable information about the composition of packaged tea - the manufacturer can add ingredients that will not be listed on the package.
Sawdust is not thrown away at the end of the season, so it can end up in tea.
"Moreover, tea plants are not always included in the bags," Tikhonova said.
According to her, it is better to abandon the use of such a drink in favor of weight tea, which is sold in specialized stores.
In addition, she stressed that the danger of packaged tea lies not only in the composition, but also in the method of its production - microparticles are heated to high temperatures, because of which they can begin to emit harmful substances.
"It is best to buy pure green or black tea - in this drink there will be the least additives," - said the expert.
