On September 27, Andrei Kutepov, Chairman of the Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy, sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and the Minister of Finance Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express a position on initiatives of the subjects of the Federation to improve legislation in the field of support for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).
It is time to establish interregional ties
The Committee of the Federation Council on Economic Policy summarized the information received from the regions about the programs of business development and legalization of self-employed people, as well as the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of SME development and sent proposals to improve existing legislation.
"Today, communication between the regions is not sufficiently established, as a result of which the business community in all regions of the visit by senators has indicated the lack of information about regional programs for the development of entrepreneurship in the country as a whole," Andrei Kutepov said.
In the annex to the letter, which was sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments of the regions on the legalization of self-employment and consolidated data from the regions with proposals and issues (available to the editorial board).
In addition to the relevant ministries, consolidated data from the regions are also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on the positively implemented developments in the regions could give an impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step to such an exchange will be to forward the information available to the Committee on Economic Policy,” the senator told Parliament’s newspaper.
Useful experience
Today, many regions of the country have adopted and successfully operate support programs for small and medium-sized businesses.
For example, in the Vologda region there is a Center for Entrepreneurship Support, which, in addition to financial support measures, helps businessmen in the certification of finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a system of business support has been developed, providing for the implementation of the single window principle through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar Territory, start-up agricultural consumer cooperatives are granted grants at the expense of the regional budget.
In the Orel region there is a cluster development center.
The Amur region within the framework of the federal project "Acceleration of small and medium-sized enterprises" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-state coworking centers at the expense of the federal budget.
And in a number of other regions, special support measures for youth entrepreneurship are being taken.
Self-employed continue to be driven out of the shadows
In the opinion of the regional authorities, a number of changes to the existing legislation should be made to better support small and medium-sized enterprises.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term “self-employment” with “entrepreneurial activity”, since this “most corresponds to the content of the state service for the promotion of self-employment of unemployed citizens”.
In the Ivanovo region, it is considered necessary to make amendments providing for the expansion of the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including activities for finishing and repairing residential premises, summer cottages, physical training classes.
Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous dairy producers with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury".
And in the Kostroma and Magadan regions advocate for the consolidation in the regulatory and legal field of the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and the directions of support for social entrepreneurship.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important ones will be developed in the form of specific draft laws," Kutepov said.
