At present, the participants of the rally, replacing each other, stand, holding a poster with the inscription "Freedom for all" and the names of convicted and arrested after uncoordinated rallies in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster are the names of Yegor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Danil Beglets, Evgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopaev, Aidar Gubaidulin, Alexei Minyailo, Sergei Fomin, Samaridin Rajabov, Nikita Chirtsov, Eduard Malyshevsky, V Malyshevsky.
On September 16, the Tver court of Moscow sentenced 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years in a general regime colony on charges of using violence against a fighter of the Russian Guard at an uncoordinated action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (Part 2 of Article 318 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustinov's preventive measure from detention to a non-exit subscription.
Thus, the petition for the release of Ustinov gained more than 112,000 signatures in a day.
Artists of the theater and cinema began a flashmob in support of a colleague.
To participate in a single picket in solidarity with the actor on September 18, a queue was lined up on the Old Square.
Human rights defenders, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests demanded a review of the case.
As reported to “Interfax” sister Ustinova Yulia, at a rally on September 29 in the capital in support of the defendants of the “Moscow case” her brother does not plan to speak.
The supply of "sanctions" to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government has estimated that supplies of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that fell under the Russian food embargo have decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to the report sent to the President of the Russian Federation Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from the sanctions countries, compared to 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period in 2013, Interfax reported.
At the same time, the cost of imported products decreased to $ 226.5 million from $ 4 billion to $ 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that have not fallen under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volumes of prohibited imports were compensated by the increase in imports from the CIS countries, Africa, Southeast Asia and Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import into Russia as part of counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official portal of legal information, noted that the validity of the rules was extended for one more year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the effect of the decree on the abolition of sanctions extended to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein and from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine "joined" this list.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo, which Moscow imposed in response to the anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed the destruction of “sanctioned” food by any legal means.
As Western sanctions continued, Russia also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, products that citizens import for personal use are not covered by this measure.
The ban does not apply to the importation of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called the destruction of food “simply immoral”, and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, the initiative to prohibit the destruction of food suitable for consumption was launched by Rospotrebnadzor in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation to the government was made by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of the Russian Federation Alexey Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and we need to think about how you can use them for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company found guilty of tax evasion
By the verdict of the Leninsky district court of the city of Cheboksary, the director of the LLC "Land and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov was found guilty of committing the crimes stipulated in paragraph "b" part 2 of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (avoidance of the use of taxes from the organization by including in the tax declaration the purpose of knowingly false information, his duty, committed in a particularly large amount) and part 2 of Article 27 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
This is reported by the press service of the investigative department of the SCR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information on incomplete transactions into the tax accounting documents of LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs, and, consequently, the amount of value-added and profit taxes payable to the organization was reduced by RUB 11.2 million.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years of imprisonment on probation.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will open in the center of the capital
The new school will open in Khamovniki.
According to Anastasia Pyatova, head of Moskomstroyinvest, all conditions for self-realization and development of children’s talents will be created there.
The educational institution decided to call the "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Russian Foreign Ministry and the Economic Development of Higher School Foundation.
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" is planned to begin next year.
The construction will be completed at the end of 2022, and in the next year will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project provides for the creation of a public, non-commercial educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," the press service of Moskomstroyinvest said.
In Chile began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
The construction of the dome of the E-ELT (European Extremely Large Telescope) building has officially begun this week, the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomy project so far, according to ESO.
Its total value is estimated by ESO to exceed one billion euros.
Most of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and the construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT get the first detailed pictures of planets outside the Solar System, stars in other galaxies, and also search for Earth's counterparts.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the surroundings of Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome has just begun, mirrors, scientific instruments and other components of the observatory scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, whose total cost was about 400 million euros, was received by the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
